    <a title="Leah" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/15797955-leah"><img alt="Leah" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1607273702p2/15797955.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1485117025?book_show_action=true">Dec 29, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Leah" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Leah" href="/user/show/15797955-leah">Leah</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780670023325" href="/book/show/11797365-escape-from-camp-14">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1485117025" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3516065245207151662">I feel so awkward giving this a star rating that I almost didn&apos;t. <br/><br/>I just don&apos;t know how to accurately review someone&apos;s life. Sure, I&apos;ve read some biographies and nonfiction, and last year around this time, I read <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/15195.The_Complete_Maus__Maus___1_2_' title='The Complete Maus (Maus, #1-2) by Art Spiegelman' rel='nofollow noopener'>The Complete Maus</a>. And it pretty much broke my heart. <br/><br/>This story did the same. It was such an informative and necessary read. I would recommend it to anyone. Harden did a good job at showing the reader Shin&apos;s story, while also showing the atrocities that are continuing to go on in North</span>
  <span id="freeText3516065245207151662" style="display:none">I feel so awkward giving this a star rating that I almost didn't. <br /><br />I just don't know how to accurately review someone's life. Sure, I've read some biographies and nonfiction, and last year around this time, I read <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/15195.The_Complete_Maus__Maus___1_2_" title="The Complete Maus (Maus, #1-2) by Art Spiegelman" rel="nofollow noopener">The Complete Maus</a>. And it pretty much broke my heart. <br /><br />This story did the same. It was such an informative and necessary read. I would recommend it to anyone. Harden did a good job at showing the reader Shin's story, while also showing the atrocities that are continuing to go on in North Korea.<br /><br />It wasn't entertaining, and I didn't find any joy in reading this story. But, it was thought provoking and a reminder to always keep my eyes and heart open, and to never close my mind to the pain and human sufferings that go on all of the world.<br /><br />When I can, I need to do what I can to help always.</span>
  <a data-text-id="3516065245207151662" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
